    "type": "message",
    "text": "I made an experimental interactive &amp; adaptive history of natural language processing (the data science subfield) - but the point isn't the topic, the point is how you can interact with the content, which is an example of what I want to do with all kinds of content - you can view and query it from any perspective:\n• <https://www.nlphistory.com/?name=A%20Brief%20General%20History&amp;q0=GetEvents&amp;q0_depth=2&amp;q0_scope=0|get a general summary>\n• see <https://www.nlphistory.com/?name=The%20Road%20to%20Sesame%20Street&amp;q0=GetEverythingOnEntity&amp;q0_entity=Transformer&amp;q0_depth=6&amp;q0_scope=16&amp;h0=0&amp;h0_entity=language%20model&amp;h0_mask=34&amp;h1=1&amp;h1_entity=Transformer&amp;h1_mask=34|how a specific technique developed over time>,\n• explore varying levels of detail,\n• jump around associatively, \nYou can also just <https://www.nlphistory.com/|start from scratch and make completely new queries> (and share a link here for the rest of us).\nI'm very curious what you all think of interacting with content like that. Imagine if you could interact with all kinds of content - web content, standard documents, code docs - with an interface like that.\n\n(I hope this is relevant, if it isn't, I'll happily delete it :))",
